<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="394" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1004,1283]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1184,1210]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe, East Mediterranean (
<collectingCountry box="[692,775,1184,1210]" name="Turkey" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[788,890,1184,1211]" name="Lebanon" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
), Transcaucasia, plains of 
<collectingCountry box="[1189,1323,1184,1210]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, Southern Siberia eastwards as far as the Baikal Lake, steppes of 
<collectingCountry box="[754,867,1220,1246]" name="Mongolia" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. In Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1055,1186,1220,1246]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
was found in only one locality, environs of Lepsinsk, low mountains of the eastern part of the Dzhungarsky Alatau Mtn. Range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
